<HTMLSourceElementMedia>
<summary>
The <strong><c>media</c></strong> property of the <see cref="HTMLSourceElement"/> interface is a string representing the intended destination medium for the resource. The value is a <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_media_queries/Using_media_queries">media query</see>, which is a comma separated list of media-types, media-features, and logical operators.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>It reflects the <c>media</c> attribute of the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/source">source</see> element.</para>
<para>-<see cref="HTMLSourceElement.Type"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLSourceElement.Sizes"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLSourceElement.Src"/><br/>-<see cref="HTMLSourceElement.Srcset"/><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/source">source</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/picture">picture</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/audio">audio</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/video">video</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_media_queries/Using_media_queries">Using media queries</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLSourceElement/media"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value>A string.</value>
</HTMLSourceElementMedia>
